romotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwytecube.showPublicProfile?language=EN>wytecube</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 3:56:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1967.topic>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Shadowzerk Updates</span><hr size=1> Have there been any new revelations on the Shadowzerker characters?<br><br>Thanks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 5:22:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1967.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> first</span><hr size=1> First revelation.  The axe-axe shadowzerk is probably superior to the sword-axe one, despite the sword having better styles.  Reason:  you will always be using magic axes in your left hand after level 20, and these will add subtantial points to axe.  These go to waste on a sword-axe zerk, but could've scaled with an axe spec shadowzerk.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukeryath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keryath</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.twitchmonkey.com/~damnskippy/DAoC/kerface.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 11:37:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1967.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.twitchmonkey.com/~damnskippy/DAoC/kerface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Just use Left Axe.</span><hr size=1> That, and Left Axe styles pretty much just smoke the base weapon styles like a Thanksgiving Day Turkey.<br><br><b>Rear Opening:</b> (for non CS)<br><i>"Gimmie mah Money"</i><br>Snowsquall -> Icy Brilliance<br><br><b>Evades:</b><br><i>"Oh please"</i><br>Comeback -> Frosty Gaze<br><br><b>Anytimes:</b><br><i>"The Yawn"</i><br>Doublefrost<br><i>"The Hot Damn"</i><br>Ravager -> Atrophy -> Scathing Blade<br><i>"The Roshambo"</i><br>Ravager -> Atrophy -> Decaying Rage<br><br>You will want to map Temper/Hoarfrost/Placate as an anytime deaggro, but that's pretty much it.<br><br>Sadly, with the exception of the big hit from PA, the Left Axe tree makes Crit Strike look like a quadriplegic pole-vaulter. I mean seriously, a three hit anytime combo that finishes with a deaggro? Are you kidding? <i>Sign me up, baby</i> <p><center><img src=http://www.twitchmonkey.com/~damnskippy/DAoC/kerysmall2.jpg></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unyvinyd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyvinyd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 2:17:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1967.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jurassic5.com/images/index_logo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just use Left Axe.</span><hr size=1> Just adding the low level aspect to this.<br><br>At level 16 my SB uses nothing but left axe styles unless for some strange reason he feels like using his great axe.   <p><center><img src=http://www.rockapella.com/IMAGES/rocktype.gif></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwytecube.showPublicProfile?language=EN>wytecube</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 11:55:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1967.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just use Left Axe.</span><hr size=1> I've already put points into sword, so I think I'm gonna stick it out with swd/la.  Hopefully the difference isn't enough to make me regret it.    <br><br>I have a 29 Shadowblade that went Axe/La so I wanted to get a different look with this one.  Kinda bored with the lvl 29, high cs, axe, la.<br><br>Thanks everyone for the responses.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaxterixenobelix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Axterix EnObelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 5:04:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1967.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just use Left Axe.</span><hr size=1> Most important revelation is this:<br>Get Doublefrost.<br><br>Other than that, we're still kicking too much butt to have time to take names<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaxterixenobelix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Axterix EnObelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 6:50:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1967.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just use Left Axe.</span><hr size=1> A new revelation:<br><br>Primary hand weapon skill seems to set the variance on left axe styles.<br><br>Alais ran a few tests of a sword (non-spec'd) vs axe (spec'd).  With sword, the doublefrost bonus was about 60% of what it was with the axe.  The sword was slightly faster (3.9 vs 4.2), but not enough to account for the difference.<br><br>This places extra value on your primary weapon skill.  To raise that, points are going to have to come from somewhere else.  As far as I can tell, the best place for this would be stealth as we don't need as much of it as a CS SB.<br><br>New Max Plan for me:<br>35 stealth<br>41 envenom<br>39 axe<br>39 left axe<br>2 CS<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=1967.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=1967.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1967.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=1967.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 